The Rays will try to get their bats going on another cold day in Chicago, as they face the White Sox at 2:10 p.m. Wander Franco, who has been one of the Rays’ few hot hitters, will get part of the day off, with DH duties rather than playing shortstop. Another of their top hitters, Ji-Man Choi, is not in the lineup, which is notable since they are facing Sox right-hander Michael Kopech. Choi was kicked in the right foot covering first base during Friday’s game and went down, but he was more scared (given a previous right ankle surgery) than hurt and stayed in. Manager Kevin Cash said that it was just a day off for Choi and that his foot was fine. The Rays are starting veteran Corey Kluber, who had a solid Tampa Bay debut on Sunday. And while the Rays’ pitching plans are not set, Cash they are still expecting Tommy Romero to pitch as either a starter or behind an opener on Sunday and are now likely to bring back lefty Shane McClanahan on regular rest to pitch Monday. Game-time temperatures are expected to be in the mid-40s. Here is the Rays lineup: And for the White Sox, under Tampa-born manager Tony La Russa: • • • Sign up for the Rays Report weekly newsletter to get fresh perspectives on the Tampa Bay Rays and the rest of the majors from sports columnist John Romano. Never miss out on the latest with the Bucs, Rays, Lightning, Florida college sports and more. Follow our Tampa Bay Times sports team on Twitter and Facebook.